  {"id":"code-explainer-deep","title":"Deep Code Explainer","category":"Code","tags":["code","explanation","learning","debugging"],"featured":False,"description":"Explain complex code in depth — covering what it does, why it is written that way, tradeoffs, and potential issues.","model_notes":{"gpt-5.4":"Max quality produces thorough explanations with analogies. Strong on algorithmic complexity.","claude-sonnet-4-6":"Lean is excellent — clear, structured explanations of complex code. Best model here.","claude-opus-4-6":"Max quality explains advanced patterns and architectural implications deeply.","gemini-3.1-pro":"Balanced is solid for most code types and languages.","grok-4":"Balanced works well for standard code explanations.","llama-4-scout":"Balanced recommended for completeness.","mistral-large-3":"Lean is reliable for common code patterns.","o1":"Max quality for understanding deeply algorithmic or mathematically complex code."},"benchmarks":{"gpt-5.4":{"lean":4,"balanced":5,"max_quality":5,"best":"max_quality"},"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"lean":5,"balanced":5,"max_quality":4,"best":"lean"},"claude-opus-4-6":{"lean":4,"balanced":5,"max_quality":5,"best":"max_quality"},"gemini-3.1-pro":{"lean":4,"balanced":5,"max_quality":4,"best":"balanced"},"grok-4":{"lean":3,"balanced":4,"max_quality":4,"best":"balanced"},"llama-4-scout":{"lean":3,"balanced":4,"max_quality":4,"best":"balanced"},"mistral-large-3":{"lean":4,"balanced":4,"max_quality":4,"best":"lean"},"o1":{"lean":3,"balanced":4,"max_quality":5,"best":"max_quality"}},"variants":{"lean":{"prompt":"Explain what this code does, line by line if needed. Note any tricky parts.\n\n[CODE]","token_estimate":20},"balanced":{"prompt":"Explain the following code to an intermediate developer.\n\nCover:\n- **What it does**: high-level purpose\n- **How it works**: walk through the logic step by step\n- **Why this approach**: design decisions and tradeoffs\n- **Potential issues**: edge cases, performance concerns, or bugs to watch for\n\nLanguage: [LANGUAGE]\n\n[CODE]","token_estimate":67},"max_quality":{"prompt":"You are a senior engineer explaining code to a developer trying to fully understand it.\n\n## Overview\nWhat does this code do? When would you use it?\n\n## Line-by-Line Walkthrough\nExplain each meaningful block. For complex expressions, break them down.\n\n## Design Decisions\n- Why was it written this way instead of alternatives?\n- What tradeoffs were made?\n- What assumptions does the code rely on?\n\n## Complexity Analysis\nTime and space complexity. Identify bottlenecks.\n\n## Edge Cases & Potential Bugs\nWhat inputs or states could break this? What is not handled?\n\n## How to Extend It\nIf someone needed to add [FEATURE], where and how would they do it?\n\nLanguage: [LANGUAGE]\nContext: [WHERE THIS CODE LIVES IN THE CODEBASE]\n\n[CODE]","token_estimate":155}}},
